The paper deals with wireless networks, their performance, and security. The use of stochastic geometry and game theory also suggests that it could belong to the sub-categories of Information Theory (cs.IT), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), Systems and Control (cs.SY), Game Theory (cs.GT), and Cryptography and Security (cs.CR). However, since the paper primarily deals with the performance and security of wireless networks, cs.IT and cs.NI are the most likely sub-categories.
